## Packagist GitHub instructions

Here are step-by-step instructions for accessing and using Packagist.com with GitHub SSO:

### Accessing Packagist.com

1. Open your web browser and navigate to [https://packagist.com/](https://packagist.com/).
2. Click the **Login with GitHub** button to access Packagist.com using your GitHub account.

### GitHub Single Sign-On (SSO)

1. You will be redirected to GitHub for authentication. If you are not already logged in to GitHub, you will be prompted to log in with your GitHub credentials.
2. Once logged in, authorize Packagist.com to access your GitHub account information.

### Linking Packagist.com with GitHub

1. After completing the authentication process, you will be redirected to Packagist.com.
2. Packagist.com will now be linked to your GitHub account, allowing you to access your GitHub repositories and packages from within Packagist.com.

### Accessing Shared Package Repository

1. Once logged in, you can access the shared repository at [https://github.com/linkorb/log-bundle](https://github.com/linkorb/log-bundle).
2. Check if you have access to the repository. You should see the contents and details of the shared repository.

## Packagist.com Credentials

1. To find your Packagist.com credentials, navigate to [https://packagist.com/orgs/linkorb](https://packagist.com/orgs/linkorb).
2. Your credentials, including API keys or access tokens, will be available on this page. Make sure to keep this information secure.

### Using Packagist.com

- With your Packagist.com account linked to GitHub, you can use Packagist.com to manage and publish Composer packages associated with your GitHub repositories.
- You can publish new packages or updates to existing packages directly from your GitHub repositories through Packagist.com.